                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that the United States embassy in Russia telegraphs that the
                    Russian minister for foreign affairs requests that Mr. Conger <pb facs="0149"
                        n="65" xml:id="pg_65"/> communicate to the Russian minister at Peking the
                    demands of the United States relative to localities to be opened to trade. He
                    promises that the minister of Russia will be authorized to frankly state to the
                    Chinese Government the attitude of Russia.</p>
                <p>Mr. Conger is instructed to confer fully with the Russian minister and report the
                    result to the Department.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
